.\" Manpage for simpleshell
.TH SIMPLE-SHELL 2023-04-27 "Manual for program ./shs"

.SH NAME
./hsh - a simple shell program
. SH SYNOPSIS
simple_shell

.SH DESCRIPTION
simple_shell is a basic shell program that provides a command-line interface for interacting with the operating system. Users can enter commands and the shell will execute them. It is designed to be a lightweight and easy-to-use alternative to more advanced shell programs like bash.

.SH OPTIONS
This program does not take any command-line options.

.SH USAGE
It is possible to use it on interactive mode and non interactive mode.
To use simple_shell, simply type commands at the prompt and press Enter. The shell will execute the command and display the output. The following are some examples of commands that can be run with simple_shell:
.TP ls - Lists the contents of the current directory.
.TP echo - Prints a message to the console.

.SH COMMANDS
The following commands are built into simple_shell:
.SS INTERACTIVE MODE:
./hsh
$ <your command>

.SS NON INTERACTIVE MODE:
echo "<your command>" | ./shs

.SH EXEMPLES
.SS INTERACTIVE MODE
./hsh
$ ls
.SS NON INTERACTIVE MODE
echo "ls" | ./shs

.SH RETURN
0: Succes
.TP
127: Command not found
.TP
128: Memory allocation fault
.TP
129: Process child fault
.TP
130: Execution command fault

.SH NOTES
This project was created in 2 weeks.

.SH BUGS
When the environement or the PATH is empty, the program failled.

